{
  "message": "test(ma): extend masked cumprod/ptp/median/argmin/argmax differential coverage\n\nAdded 9 fixtures targeting thin MaskedArray ops (complementary to\ncod's cumsum axis work \u2014 this commit covers cumprod + reductions):\n\n- cumprod axis=0/axis=1 on 2x3 with sparse mask \u2014 verifies per-column\n  and per-row scanning with 1-fill for masked cells, mask preserved\n- ptp on 2D with masked max (unmasked range 1..6 minus 2 \u2192 5),\n  ptp spanning a negative range with masked extreme ([5,100,-50,0]\n  after masking -100 \u2192 150)\n- median on 7-element alternating mask (unmasked [1,3,5,7] \u2192 4.0)\n- argmin axis=0 and axis=1 on 2x3 with one masked cell that would\n  otherwise be the row/column winner\n- argmax axis=0 and axis=1 on the same shape \u2014 verifies the masked\n  argmax still skips the masked position\n\n78 masked_differential cases total (from 69).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
